author: @user-dr2yz8um3d
text:
1 year old already!!!

I saw this with my older sister and her boyfriend 
Crazy this is director James Gunn's last outing since he's going to be in charge of the next wave of movies for DC

The villain here the High Evolutionary is made of narcissism, zealotry, and single-mindedness obsessed with perfection 
Even though the movie is 2 hours and 29 min it gets by with all these actors as these characters 
9 years they become people whoâ€™s pasts are not squeaky clean, they learn to get past the trauma theyve experienced 

Again I admit several parts I wasn't expecting to cry
Especially around Rocket's dark origins, they insert a big commentary on perfecting a species and animal experimentation
Not to mention an anti-fascist message
I still wanted Adam Warlock to be more of a central villain because Will Poulter is a good actor be he feels lost in the shuffle
But the movie does a great job wrapping up this trilogy and making this rag tag team of heroes leave quite the mark
All of them have their respective stories tied up in a nice bow
Glad the action is cool, the effects, the laughs, and the tender moments work without being interrupted by a corny joke
The production design is quite colorful and the makeup effects with the costumes
Thereâ€™s the hands that created us and then thereâ€™s the hands that guide us, we donâ€™t have to spend our days hating ourselves, stupid people still make us laugh, nobody asks to be perfected or improved, when God isnâ€™t around someone else steps in

author: @BensCoffeeRants
text:
Overall Great movie, Loved it.  I immediately recognized the Laika (Russian Astronaut dog) reference and was saddened by this, although this puts an optimistic spin on that story dog somehow survived to gain telekinetic powers (help from some friendly aliens?) perhaps this twist was inspired by the brilliant fan made music video for Sharon Van Ettens 'I Can't Breathe" song which on its own is already depressing enough, search for the video, "I Can't Breathe, Sharon Van Etten, Laika" 

Spoiler Alert: 

One thing that bothered me also related to the dog was the whole bad dog thing, it was an obvious and lame set up which I saw coming a mile away, plus the whole reason the guy was saying bad dog was purely because he was jealous the dog did something better than him and was insecure, which is pretty pathetic of his character especially after the dog repeatedly lets him know how much that bothers him, only after the dog saves his life is the dog redeemed to be a 'good boy' again... That's a D*ck Move! 

And the bad guy is supposed to so smart, yet doesn't realize sometimes getting an outside perspective can be beneficial in solving problems, and that different people, or creatures have different types or areas of intelligence.  If everyone was equally smart and did things in the exact same way, it would be pretty boring I think. 
Also with all that bio tech, he couldn't have fixed himself a better face? :D  Literally cut and paste is the best he's got !? :D

author: @BlazinNSoul
text:
Loved this even more then the last one was kinda fell flat. I especially was intrigued by Mantis this time  and the outstanding performance from the High Evolutionary in Chukwudi Iwuji. With a few more edits it would have been even better. 

Now with Pom Klementieff clearly moving into bigger roles with Mission Impossible Dead Reckoning. I hope her charcter also moves in more interesting directions within the MCU. 

Given her direct connections with the Kree & the Priests of Parma. As well as within Secret Wars. Of which she has a direct role as part of the Dragons of Shang Chi. 

There are several alternative realities i could see this go. Overall Guardians 3 was over far to soon & in some ways missed opertunites. As we could have gotten more from The Collector. Which is more central to the entire MCU then some might think. I hope he retuns in the future. :)

text: Excellent movie. I read reviews before it came out, and I don't believe the blowhards coming up with the ridiculous criticisms. Better than GoG2 IMO, and a great ending to the trilogy. author: @CaptainVelveeta
text: I feel like GOTG3 made the same mistake "Thor - Love and Thunder" made. Don't get me wrong, 1 and 2 are a couple of my favorite Marvel movies ever but 3 , like Love and Thunder, felt gratuitous and long-winded. It was very predictable and seemed a little stale at times. Also, to be successful with any two and a half hour movie, you need a very, very strong storyline and I don't think they had that.

author: @krabkrabby
text:
Ok, I really thought this would have been total cr@p. I can't suffer any marvel movie of the least years and I'm not a fan of Guardians of the galaxy. Heck, I think that 1st movie is terrible and 2nd is pretty bad.
I'm so surprised I was wrong!
guys, literally... This movie ROCKS!
Not for kids anyway. It has very mature thematics and explicit violence, so not exactly pg13. More like pg16.
It's very good. The story is interesting and with a good writing, the villain is a very well done psycho (the actor is astonishing), main characters are all memorable and funny and it's full of good messages.
It gives very positive and optimistic vibes! At the end of the movie you really care for everyone and you want to see what will happen to them all.
What can I say? I thought James Gunn was a lazy incompetent, but it turned out he's very good. I'm genuinely very glad to say that this movie was a very good work. My compliment to all the artists who worked on it. ALSO, CGI was very cheap in previous movies, but they have done a marvelous job here.
That was a beautiful experience, thank you for having done a great movie after all these years! ğŸ˜

Racoon (sorry rocket, weâ€™re from the real world). It was horrific. This is no longer childâ€™s play. author: @limphocyticpredominance38
text:
[mild spoiler alert]

What I loved most about this movie is that it wasn't dealing with some multiversal threat that required me to watch previous TV series, with cliffhangers that left me waiting for the Next Big Movie for the payoff.

Instead, it told a self-contained story with lots of heart about characters I previously knew nothing about, but learned to slowly love and appreciate -- including a tree that only says three words, and an abrasive rodent. But somehow I left that theater in tears, full of love and laughter for the last 2.5 hours that zoomed by. Amidst the size that the MCU has achieved, I consider this the true Marvel cinematic experience <3

author: @ch1701a
text:
I can't wait to see this new Guardians of the Galaxy movie.  
It's the last Marvel movie director Tommy Gunn is making before he goes to Warner Bros to make the new Harry Potter DCU movies, so you know he is going to put in a lot of Easter eggs and tie the 2 franchises together.  
It's going to be interesting to see if Chris Evan's character, Peter Quilt, and Zoe Kravitz's character, Kimora, get back together.  I like that 'Will They' or 'Won't They' playful banter.  
I aslo heard that Hulk Hogan who plays Traxx, requested that his character be killed off so he could follow director Tommy Gunn to Warner Bros to do the Harry Potter DCU movies.  
They must have got an AI to do the character of Root's voice, which was done by Paul Walker in the previous Guardians of the Galaxy movies because Root is all grown up in this movie and Paul Walker is dead.  
I heard in this movie, Bradley Cooper's character, Space Racoon, gets a love interest.  CGI is amazing at how they can fit Bradley Cooper into the Space Racoon suit.  
I also heard that this movie is making the LBGTQ community happy with the relationship that develops between Mathis and Kimora's sister, Neptuna.  I really didn't expect that but Disney had to do something to make the public happy after that whole She-Hulk debacle.
Anyway, can't wait to see this when it comes out on the pirated streaming sites.  Phase 18 of the Marvel Universe has sucked so far so hopefully they can redeem themselves with this movie.

author: @davidn4125
text: One of the top 10 worst movies I have ever seen.  I am sick of movies that supplement weak plot lines with music and cute animals to get an emotional response from the audience.  Could not wait until it was over.  If you liked Jurassic Park 3 you will like this movie. The movie starts off with this Warlock character infiltrating the Guardian compound to capture Rocket because the High Evolutionary needs to study him.  So what's the first thing Warlock does when he meets Rocket?  He basically kills him with a blast to the chest if it weren't for the efforts of the rest of the Guardians to keep him alive.  What?  Doesn't the high evolutionary need him alive to study him?  Oh never mind just don't think about it too much.  From there the movie continues it's downward spiral with ridiculous plot twists that come out of nowhere with little explanation.  And there is this ridiculous plot line where the Guardians land on this earth like planet run by genetically engineered animals who just so happen to drive around in 1980's Ford's and Chevy's. WHAT?!?!?  Oh, never mind just don't think about it.  And while on this planet Drax clotheslines some poor innocent guy riding by on a Motorcycle to steal his bike.  It looks like he killed the guy since he's lying in the street not moving.   I felt sorry for the guy lying in the street and hated Drax's character at that point.  Good job Disney with character development.  By the way ... the scene where Drax calls the imprisoned children idiots and morons was so cringe worthy I almost had to leave the theater.

author: @peterberg8417
text: Theaters need to offer more variety again especially for adults who are sick of these childish super hero movies dominating every multiplex. It saddens me that films like the Fabelmans (directed by one of the greatest directors of our time) flops at the box office while these brainless superhero movies lap up the audience's money. Unfortunately that shows the dumbing down of the audience and how the attention spans of functioning adults can't appreciate a drama with great dialogue and cinematography over a kid's movie like this. Adults are regressing and culture is suffering because of it. Luckily, there are tons of movies from like pre-2017 that I can go back to watch that give me a mature story for anyone over the age of 16, but it saddens me that we will be getting less movies like that in theaters because average people cannot be bothered to think or challenge their brains for 2 hours anymore. This all started when Disney bought Fox and crushed Fox Searchlight Studios, relegating those films to streaming where nobody will see them and they won't enter the cultural zeitgeist. Fox was the last of the major studios offering adult films. Yes, we have A24 but that is a minor studio and is basically a footnote in the film world these days. Even if Everything Everywhere All at Once (one of their films) won best picture at the Oscars, the Oscars are losing their influence over movie-goers due to many reasons that I won't go into so a best picture win does not hold as much value as it used to. And it doesn't help that Everything Everywhere All at Once is basically a superhero movie anyway. RIP American intelligence and thought. I fear for the future when the TikTok generation takes over and becomes tasked with curating and preserving the art and literature of our past because I fear they will just cancel it all outright for challenging their perception of the world in which they live.

author: @steveness2501
text: Strictly speaking for myself, Guardians Of The Galaxy is the MCU at it's very best.  These movies do stand on their own while feeling every bit as important and impactful as any other MCU film. They are just so insanely awesome in a way that you feel you KNOW these characters. You understand them and feel their emotions and humor (or lack thererof) from the moment you are first introduced to them. These characters are so seriously flawed in a way we all are. From the first film, you can pretty much relate to what each and every character is feeling. The writing, casting, acting is insane.  Even something as simple as Glenn Close' "prick" comment in the first film. You immediately can relate to her situation and feeling even though her situation is so absurdly beyond our experience.  I adore these characters and am very thankful they exist. To everyone involved in bringing them to the big screen all the way to when each debuted in comic book lore... thank you.

text:
Jesus is God & He loves you

Jesus will soon be seen by all men, women, and children in the clouds. Jesus is returning now! Believe and be saved.

Exodus 3:14 (God speaking)
And God said unto Moses, I AM THAT I AM: and he said, Thus shalt thou say unto the children of Israel, I AM hath sent me unto you.

John 8:58 (Jesus speaking)
Jesus said unto them, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Before Abraham was, I am.

John 10:30 (Jesus speaking)
I and my Father are one.

Isaiah 9:6
For unto us a child is born, unto us a son is given: and the government shall be upon his shoulder: and his name shall be called Wonderful, Counsellor, The mighty God, *The everlasting Father,* The Prince of Peace.

Matthew 1:23
Behold, a virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth a son, and they shall call his name Emmanuel, which being interpreted is, *God with us.*

John 1:1 & 14
1 In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.
14 And the Word was made flesh (Lord Jesus), and dwelt among us, (and we beheld his glory, the glory as of the only begotten of the Father,) full of grace and truth.

John 8:24 (Jesus speaking)
I said therefore unto you, that ye shall die in your sins: for if ye believe not that I am he, ye shall die in your sins.

John 14:9 (Jesus speaking)
Jesus saith unto him, Have I been so long time with you, and yet hast thou not known me, Philip? he that hath seen me hath seen the Father; and how sayest thou then, Show us the Father?

Hebrews 1:1-3, & 8 (God calls His Son "O God" because Jesus IS God in the flesh)
1 God, who at sundry times and in divers manners spake in time past unto the fathers by the prophets,
2 Hath in these last days spoken unto us by his Son, whom he hath appointed heir of all things, by whom also he made the worlds;
3 Who being the brightness of his glory, and the express image of his person, and upholding all things by the word of his power, when he had by himself purged our sins, sat down on the right hand of the Majesty on high;
8 But unto the Son he saith, Thy throne, O God, is for ever and ever: a sceptre of righteousness is the sceptre of thy kingdom.

1 John 5:7
For there are three that bear record in heaven, the Father, the Word, and the Holy Ghost: and these three are one.

Titus 2:13!!!
Looking for that blessed hope, and the glorious appearing of the great God and our Saviour Jesus Christ;

Revelation 1:7
Behold, he cometh with clouds; *and every eye shall see him,* and they also which pierced him: and all kindreds of the earth shall wail because of him. Even so, Amen.

Isaiah 44:6 (God speaking)
Thus saith the LORD the King of Israel, and his redeemer the LORD of hosts; I am the first, and I am the last; and beside me there is no God.

Revelation 1:8 (Jesus speaking)
I am Alpha and Omega, the beginning and the ending, saith the Lord, which is, and which was, and which is to come, *the Almighty.*

Revelation 22:13 (Jesus speaking)
I am Alpha and Omega, the beginning and the end, the first and the last.

---

There Are None Righteous / How To Be Saved

Romans 3:10 & 23
10 As it is written, There is none righteous, no, not one:!!!
23 For all have sinned, and come short of the glory of God;

Luke 5:31-32 (Jesus speaking)
31 And Jesus answering said unto them, They that are whole need not a physician; but they that are sick.
32 I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.

1 Peter 3:18 (The word â€œquickenâ€ means â€œto make aliveâ€)
For Christ also hath once suffered for sins, the just for the unjust, that he might bring us to God, being put to death in the flesh, but quickened by the Spirit:

Romans 10:9
That if thou shalt confess with thy mouth the Lord Jesus, and shalt believe in thine heart that God hath raised him from the dead, thou shalt be saved.

Acts 4:12
Neither is there salvation in any other: for there is none other name under heaven given among men, whereby we must be saved.

Ephesians 2:8-9
8 For by grace are ye saved through faith; and that not of yourselves: it is the gift of God:
9 Not of works, lest any man should boast.

Repent of your sins or suffer the consequences. Lord Jesus died in our places personally to take the death punishment that sin deserves and then resurrected by the power of God. Believe this and sincerely repent of your sins each time you sin and you will have eternal life and nothing to fear. Fail to repent and you will end up in the Lake of Fire.

Just seeing Lylla finally in the MCU despite the fact that Vol. 3 is the final chapter in the Gotg story is a dream come true.

I know a lot people think & say Rocket is gonna die just based on what the trailers are representing what is gonna go down in the film, but I honestly think itâ€™s a way to throw people off and show that it will in fact be someone else in the guardians. I will not say who I think it will be, but Iâ€™m almost confident itâ€™s not Rocket.

Out of all things shown so far, Iâ€™m honestly looking forward to seeing Rocket & Lyllaâ€™s relationship, theyâ€™ve had a romantic history together (as her name was shown for Rocket in the interrogation scene in Vol. 1), and I have a feeling in a positive way that theyâ€™ll be one of, if not the best couple ever written in the MCU, and theyâ€™re not even human characters. 

Iâ€™m prepared but at the same time not prepared for the emotions this movie will bring, not just for Rocketâ€™s backstory and someone potentially getting killed off (again, not Rocket, but someone within the guardians), but also Lyllaâ€™s character as well, she will definitely be equally as important as the High Evolutionary as he â€œcreatedâ€ both her & Rocket.
